Articles.Content: thank you for the update and the Thread, @Waz

5 minutes ago, Waz said:

@Galileo - if I could look at exactly the files you're using rather than just some random SVE version, we could narrow down the cause. I'm using a GTX980 on Windows 10. KSP x64, no special command line options.

Why are you needing to use weird color settings like that though? The SVE I've got is 255,255,255,240.

that was just a test. The brighter i set them the darker they got it was wierd. Im testing something now

I just did a clean install of 1.2 and the issues went away.. very strange. Sorry for thinking it was a bug man. You rock. perhaps i need to start following my own troubleshooting advice that i give out all the time...

@Waz i figured out how to replicate the wierd bugs i was experiencing. Changing any value in the GUI and hitting apply causes the issues. the only way to remedy the problems is a scene change.

 

Edited October 12, 2016 by Galileo

1 hour ago, Galileo said:

 

@Waz i figured out how to replicate the wierd bugs i was experiencing. Changing any value in the GUI and hitting apply causes the issues. the only way to remedy the problems is a scene change.

 

Ouch. That'll make it pretty clumsy to edit configs. Could you file an Issue on my EVE github with exact replication details. In the end, a useful thing to know, so well worth the path to finding it!

2 minutes ago, Waz said:

Ouch. That'll make it pretty clumsy to edit configs. Could you file an Issue on my EVE github with exact replication details. In the end, a useful thing to know, so well worth the path to finding it!

Actually i have found editing in the tracking station avoids the bugs. The only down side to that is you lose the capability to edit volumetric clouds. Ill file an issue for you
Issue has been filed

I did a fresh bare minimum install still did not work   http://imgur.com/am2Q57I
